<item>
<title>Trois croissants!</title>
<description>&lt;p&gt;So who persuaded the mighty Sir Chris Hoy to appear in this &lt;a href="http://www.kelloggs.co.uk/whatson/branflakes"&gt;silly advert&lt;/a&gt;?
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.kelloggs.co.uk/whatson/branflakes"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3266/3143569701_b391017074_d.jpg" alt="Chris Hoy advertises Bran Flakes"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;
     Poking fun at the French isn&amp;#8217;t smart.
 &lt;/li&gt;

 &lt;li&gt;
     Mocking their cycling decline is like kicking someone who&amp;#8217;s already down.
 &lt;/li&gt;

 &lt;li&gt;
     Bran flakes are sugar and chaff &amp;#8212; hardly suitable for someone who burns lots of energy.
 &lt;/li&gt;

 &lt;li&gt;
     Croissants are delicious. Maybe not something for every day. But delicious!
 &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;span id="continue-reading"/&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;#8217;s a proper breakfast food. One I&amp;#8217;d be happy to see the Scottish sprint knight advertising.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.historyworld.co.uk/advert.php?id=1286&amp;amp;offset=0&amp;amp;sort=0&amp;amp;l1=Food&amp;amp;l2=Cereals"&gt; &lt;img src="http://www.historyworld.co.uk/content/scotts3.jpg" alt="Scott's porridge Oats" width="300px"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Like Sir Chris, Alex needs real fuel. This morning he ate three croissants.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/thomasguest/3358728547/" title="Alex in garden by Thomas Guest, on Flickr"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3541/3358728547_0b32956de7_o.jpg" width="400px" alt="Alex in garden" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description>
<dc:date>2009-03-16</dc:date>
<guid>http://tag.wordaligned.org/posts/trois-croissants</guid>
